# TYPING RULE: bounded-quantification well-formedness — a declared trait
# bound must actually constrain a used type.
#
# Prior art: bounded parametric polymorphism's well-formedness condition
# (classically F<:, bounded System F — Cardelli & Wegner, "On Understanding
# Types, Data Abstraction, and Polymorphism", ACM Computing Surveys 17(4),
# 1985) specialized to Rust trait bounds per the Rust Reference's "Trait and
# lifetime bounds" section and Oxide's generic-function well-formedness
# side-condition (Weiss et al., arXiv:1903.00982, section 3). For Rust
# specifically: a generic parameter that is declared but never used anywhere
# in the item's own signature is a real, named rustc/clippy diagnostic —
# for impl blocks it is rustc error E0207 ("the type parameter is not
# constrained by the impl trait, self type, or predicates"); for standalone
# functions (this rule's target class, gec:FunctionSignature, not
# gec:TraitImpl/gec:InherentImpl) the equivalent is clippy's
# `extra_unused_type_parameters` lint, since an unused function-level type
# parameter still compiles under rustc alone. This rule checks the function
# case only — the impl-block/E0207 case is declared in this comment but not
# separately encoded because no grounded fixture in this corpus has a
# TraitImpl/InherentImpl with an unbounded-*or*-bounded generic param that
# goes unreferenced (both grounded InCore inherent impls, 有無<値> and
# 成否<成功,失敗>, DO reference their params — see gec:TypeParamRef usage in
# fixtures/gec-facts.ttl).
#
# ggen template pattern this checks:
#   packs/affidavit-pack/templates/affidavit_types.rs.tmpl:186
#   `fn canonical_bytes<T: Serialize>(value: &T) -> Result<Vec<u8>, serde_json::Error>`
#   — gec:Fn_canonical_bytes. T's gec:paramBound "Serialize" is discharged: T
#   is referenced via gec:TypeParamRef inside the parameter's ReferenceType
#   (`&T`), so the bound is not vacuous.
#
# Verified 2026-07-21: ASK=false against ontology.ttl+fixtures/gec-facts.ttl
# (canonical_bytes's T:Serialize is used); ASK=true against an adversarial
# fixture asserting a FunctionSignature with a bounded TypeGenericParam
# ("U: Clone") that appears nowhere in its parameter or return types.
PREFIX gec: <http://seanchatmangpt.github.io/packs/rust-dialect#>
ASK {
  ?sig a gec:FunctionSignature ;
       gec:genericParam ?gp .
  ?gp a gec:TypeGenericParam ; gec:paramName ?pname ; gec:paramBound ?bound .
  FILTER NOT EXISTS {
    ?sig (gec:hasParameter/gec:paramType|gec:returnType) ?anyType .
    ?anyType (gec:referent|gec:argType|gec:elementType|gec:tupleComponent)* ?ref .
    ?ref a gec:TypeParamRef ; gec:refersToParam ?pname .
  }
}
